      <title>Getting pretty in the city of Sydney: Gallo Hair</title>
      <link>http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/beauty-tips/hair-treatment-sydney/?utm_source=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=hair-treatment-sydney</link>
      <comments>http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/beauty-tips/hair-treatment-sydney/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 09 Apr 2012 09:49:41 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Little Miss Makeup</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Beauty Tips]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Australian hair and beauty]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[hair treatment sydney]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/?p=6352</guid>
      <description>When I entered Gallo Hair, I was greeted with a warm smile from Kam (aka Mr Hair Extraordinaire). Things were off to a good start: one, I had just found free on-street parking right outside; and two, I was inside a trendy downtown salon and felt welcome. My first impressions. This salon bucks stereotypes, and [...]&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/beauty-tips/hair-treatment-sydney/"&gt;Getting pretty in the city of Sydney: Gallo Hair&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog"&gt;Little Miss Makeup&amp;#039;s Blog&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/little-miss-makeups-blog/Little_Miss_Makeups_Blog-Getting_pretty_in_the_city_of_Sydney-_Gallo_Hair.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>When I entered Gallo Hair, I was greeted with a warm smile from Kam (aka Mr Hair Extraordinaire). Things were off to a good start: one, I had just found free on-street parking right outside; and two, I was inside a trendy downtown salon and felt welcome.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.gallohair.com/"><img class="size-full wp-image-6354 aligncenter" title="Gallo Hair Frontage" src="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Gallo-Hair-Frontage.png" alt="Gallo Hair Frontage Getting pretty in the city of Sydney: Gallo Hair" width="471" height="654" /></a></p>
<p><strong>My first impressions.</strong></p>
<p><em>This salon bucks stereotypes, and I like it. A lot. </em></p>
<p>As I was guided to my seat, the first thing that struck me was the slick interior and friendly vibe.</p>
<p>The salon was abuzz: hair dryers humming, color consultations under way, and customers smiling and laughing. The staff were busy, but the atmosphere didn’t feel hectic and out of control.</p>
<p>After I was seated, I was promptly delivered a peppermint tea and a chocolate-dipped, heart-shaped cookie coated in sprinkles. At this point, the stresses of my day were already slowly starting to ebb away. I sat back, watched and absorbed.</p>
<p>The most obvious thing to me was the conduct of the staff. They were interactive, professional and pleasant, and not in any way pretentious. If these hairdressers have egos, they definitely wear them on the inside. It was very apparent from my observations that they have a genuine interest in their clients. I was impressed.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.gallohair.com/"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-6358" title="Gallo Hair Interior" src="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Gallo-Hair-Interior.png" alt="Gallo Hair Interior Getting pretty in the city of Sydney: Gallo Hair" width="636" height="446" /></a><span id="more-6352"></span></p>
<p><strong>The treatment.</strong></p>
<p>After just enough time had passed, Kam arrived at my side and the conversation started. He asked me what I wanted to achieve from the day’s session, and in short, I explained that I would love my tortured tresses converted into a full-bodied, voluminous mane. A big ask? Yes. Mission impossible? Maybe. My locks are long and poker-straight – cared for to a point, but colored and blasted with a high-heat hair dryer on an all-too-regular basis. Kam was not fazed by my request. My wish was his command.</p>
<p>Armed with some of the best products in the business (Moroccanoil and Sebastian, I’m looking at you), Kam was on the case. I was escorted to the basin. My hair was washed, the treatment applied, and I was given the best scalp massage ever. My toes are tingling right now just thinking about it. My head was then origami-wrapped (a total work of art), and I was returned to my seat and positioned beneath a dryer so the treatment could be heat-processed (to aid absorption).</p>
<p>Like magic, another tea and freckled biscuit arrived along with a pile of new-release mags. I love this kind of attention and was totally lapping it up.</p>
<p>Post-heat, my hair was rinsed and dried. Using a combination of his fingers, a big-barrelled brush and Kevin Murphy Body Builder Mousse (to give extra oomph without crunch), Kam blow-dried my hair, pinning up sections as he worked to help maintain the volume – all the while chatting away happily.</p>
<div id="attachment_6356" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 514px"><a href="http://www.gallohair.com/"><img class=" wp-image-6356    " title="Kam" src="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Kam.png" alt="Kam Getting pretty in the city of Sydney: Gallo Hair" width="504" height="354" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Kam: such a darling!</p></div>
<p><strong>The results.</strong></p>
<p>The transformation was dramatic. Did my locks go from limp to luscious? Hell, yes!</p>
<p>When I stepped out of the salon, I felt a million bucks. I was rocking shiny strands, which I could swoosh from side to side like the ladies in the TV commercials. My hair had flexible fullness and gentle movement, was understated and not overstyled . . . plus, it smelled delicious.</p>
<p>Mirrors were a magnet to me for the rest of the day. In fact, at any given opportunity I couldn’t help but grab a glimpse of myself in any reflective surface: shop windows, car bumpers, you name it. I loved my new ’do.</p>
<p>The next day it was still gorgeous. And long into the weeks after, I’m still seeing the benefits.</p>
<p><strong><em>The verdict: Gallo give good hair! Book your treatment with Kam now on (02) 9360 1192, or visit <a title="GalloHair.com" href="http://www.gallohair.com/">gallo hair.com</a>.</em></strong></p>
<p><em>Words by Nita O. ♥ A 30-something, brown-eyed brunette who knows what she likes. ♥ Prefers beauty products that deliver results over those that simply look pretty. ♥ Predominantly dry/sensitive-skinned. ♥ An eco-conscious city dweller with scientific tendencies. ♥ Loves ginger cats.</em></p>
<p><a href="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/beauty-tips/hair-treatment-sydney/">Getting pretty in the city of Sydney: Gallo Hair</a> is a post from: <a href="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog">Little Miss Makeup&#039;s Blog</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
