    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Face Oil: Friend or Foe?</title>
      <link>http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/skincare-product-reviews/best-facial-oil/?utm_source=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=best-facial-oil</link>
      <comments>http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/skincare-product-reviews/best-facial-oil/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 02 Apr 2012 09:27:59 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Little Miss Makeup</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Skincare Product Reviews]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[best facial oil]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/?p=6294</guid>
      <description>“You’re glowing.” “Your skin looks great.” Isn’t that what every girl wants to hear? Lately I have been inundated with these sorts of remarks. You want to know the best part? It is my real skin they’re talking about. No foundation, concealer or highlighter in sight. Just pure, unmasked skin. The ultimate in compliments, right? [...]&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/skincare-product-reviews/best-facial-oil/"&gt;Face Oil: Friend or Foe?&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog"&gt;Little Miss Makeup&amp;#039;s Blog&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/little-miss-makeups-blog/Little_Miss_Makeups_Blog-Face_Oil-_Friend_or_Foe.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.adorebeauty.com.au/clarins/clarins-santal-face-treatment-oil-new.html"><img class="wp-image-6297 alignright" title="Clarins Santal Face Treatment Oil" src="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Clarins-Santal-Face-Treatment-Oil.png" alt="Clarins Santal Face Treatment Oil Face Oil: Friend or Foe?" width="335" height="370" /></a></p>
<p>“You’re glowing.” “Your skin looks great.” Isn’t that what every girl wants to hear? Lately I have been inundated with these sorts of remarks. You want to know the best part? It is my real skin they’re talking about. No foundation, concealer or highlighter in sight. Just pure, unmasked skin. The ultimate in compliments, right?</p>
<p><strong>The secret: Clarins Santal Face Treatment Oil.</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>For the last two months, I have been using Clarins Santal Face Treatment Oil in place of my regular moisturizer both morning and night, and the results have been spectacular.<span id="more-6294"></span></p>
<p><strong>The good oil or what?</strong></p>
<p>Face oils have long been used as an alternative to, or in conjunction with, traditional moisturizing creams and lotions. But many people still struggle with the concept of putting an oil on their face. It seems that some wrongly associate oils with evil not good, and have horrifying visions of a greasy complexion, pimples and blocked pores. In fact, these thoughts are so widespread that I’ve heard some companies market their face oils as serums in order to shake the stereotype.</p>
<p>While using a face oil on dry skin seems to be more generally accepted – not surprisingly, I guess – applying one to an oily skin is a concept that seems counterintuitive to most. But the fact is, facial oils can actually effectively normalize the production of sebum (the skin’s natural moisturizer), which means they can assist both dry and oilier skin types (by increasing and decreasing sebum production levels, respectively). The key is to pick the right oil for your skin’s needs.</p>
<p><strong>The facts.</strong></p>
<p>Clarins Face Treatment Oils:<strong></strong></p>
<ul>
<li><em><strong>⋆</strong> are made from 100% pure plant extracts. Natural plant oils have a particularly good affinity with the skin because their chemical structure is more similar to sebum than mineral- or petroleum-derived oils, which makes them easier for the skin to absorb.</em></li>
<li><em><strong>⋆</strong> come packaged in a functional glass bottle complete with a dropper for dispensing. The design is practical and purposeful, with a modern-day medicinal feel – you know, the type of packaging that proclaims: “I contain a product that works.” (And, for the record, it’s not lying.) Also, I love the way it looks in my bathroom.</em></li>
<li><em><strong>⋆</strong> were launched in 1965, and the original formula is still on the market today. That means women have been enjoying the benefits of Clarins Face Treatment Oils for almost 50 years. That alone has to be a tribute to their greatness, surely!</em></li>
</ul>
<p>Clarins Santal Face Treatment Oil is designed for dry complexions (which pretty well describes my whole face, with the exception of my nose). It:</p>
<ul>
<li><em><em><strong>⋆</strong></em> absorbs quickly.</em></li>
<li><em><strong>⋆</strong> nourishes, soothes and smooths dry skin, leaving it soft and comfortable. For the last eight weeks, I have applied several drops to my face and neck morning and night (avoiding my nose because it has a tendency to be a little oily), and the positive comments about my complexion have been non-stop! To achieve a dewy-looking décolletage, first thing in the morning – post-shower – I apply a few drops on to my damp skin, and the effect lasts all day.</em></li>
<li><em><strong>⋆</strong> protects the surface of the skin without any trace of residue.</em></li>
<li><em><strong>⋆</strong> diminishes dehydration, reduces redness and leaves the complexion beaming with radiance.</em></li>
<li><em><strong>⋆</strong> smells gloriously herbaceous. I found the fragrance very uplifting. Most face oils I have tried in the past have had a sweeter, more floral aroma, so this was a pleasant change. The sandalwood in the blend gives a hint of warmth, while the cardamom and lavender invoke feelings of relaxation and calmness.</em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The conclusion.</strong></p>
<p>Clarins Santal Face Treatment Oil is not only an excellent way to show your skin some love, but also enhance your state of well-being. Besides its beautifying and skin-nurturing benefits, I found the application process incredibly therapeutic. <em>Taking a few minutes out to spend on me. Warming the oil up in my hands. Pressing it over my face. Eyes closed. Drawing in long breaths. Absolute sensory bliss.</em> I can’t think of a better way to begin and end each day.</p>
<p><em><strong>Clarins Face Treatment Oils. I’ll admit it: I’m converted.</strong></em></p>
<p>Buy Clarins Santal Face Treatment Oil online from: <a title="Clarins.com" href="http://www.clarinsusa.com/Santal-Face-Treatment-Oil/C010401001,en_US,pd.html?start=3&amp;cgid=270" rel="nofollow">Clarins.com</a>, <a title="Clarins.co.uk" href="http://www.clarins.co.uk/Santal%20Face%20Treatment%20Oil%20%27Dry/Extra%20Dry%20Skin%27/C010401001,en_GB,pd.html&amp;cgid=270&amp;start=3" rel="nofollow">Clarins.co.uk</a> and <a title="AdoreBeauty.com.au" href="http://www.adorebeauty.com.au/clarins/clarins-santal-face-treatment-oil-new.html" rel="nofollow">Adore Beauty.com.au</a>, or visit your nearest Clarins counter.</p>
<p>Meet the other members of the Clarins Face Treatment Oil family: <a title="Blue Orchid" href="http://www.adorebeauty.com.au/clarins/clarins-blue-orchid-face-treatment-oil-new.html" rel="nofollow">Blue Orchid</a> (for dehydrated skin) and <a title="Lotus" href="http://www.adorebeauty.com.au/clarins/clarins-lotus-face-treatment-oil-new.html" rel="nofollow">Lotus</a> (for oily or combination skin).</p>
<p><em>Words by Nita O. ♥ A 30-something, brown-eyed brunette who knows what she likes. ♥ Prefers beauty products that deliver results over those that simply look pretty. ♥ Predominantly dry/sensitive-skinned. ♥ An eco-conscious city dweller with scientific tendencies. ♥ Loves ginger cats.</em></p>
<p><a href="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog/skincare-product-reviews/best-facial-oil/">Face Oil: Friend or Foe?</a> is a post from: <a href="http://littlemissmakeup.com/blog">Little Miss Makeup&#039;s Blog</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
